<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="30.[707,1194,194,1039]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[731,845,327,348]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is named for the collector of the 
<typeStatus box="[833,919,354,375]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">holotype</typeStatus>
, Edwin Fairburn.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="30.[707,1194,194,1039]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[731,836,380,401]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is similar in appearance to other members of this species-group but can be distinguished by the shape of the antennae and genitalia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="30.[707,1194,194,1039]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[731,855,486,507]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Description.</emphasis>
Length 
<quantity box="[953,1039,486,507]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" unit="mm" value="2.7">2.7 mm</quantity>
. Body brown, antennae, elytra, maxillary palpi, and legs yellowish brown (
<figureCitation box="[854,939,539,560]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="25.[175,207,1562,1581]" captionTargetBox="[158,1164,200,1538]" captionTargetId="figure-1@25.[151,1171,183,1548]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Fig. 11. Habitus of Sagola species in the bifida species-group, dorsal views. a) S. bifida, b) S. latistriata, c) S. crawi, d) S. earlyi, e) S. embersoni, f) S. mayae, g) S. ranatungae, h) S. baylessae, i) S. tekoauensis, j) S. ferroi, k) S. fairburni. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4907771" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4907771/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 11k</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[958,1019,539,560]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Head:</emphasis>
As long as wide, widest across eyes (
<figureCitation box="[920,1011,566,587]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="25.[175,207,1562,1581]" captionTargetBox="[158,1164,200,1538]" captionTargetId="figure-1@25.[151,1171,183,1548]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Fig. 11. Habitus of Sagola species in the bifida species-group, dorsal views. a) S. bifida, b) S. latistriata, c) S. crawi, d) S. earlyi, e) S. embersoni, f) S. mayae, g) S. ranatungae, h) S. baylessae, i) S. tekoauensis, j) S. ferroi, k) S. fairburni. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4907771" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4907771/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 11k</figureCitation>
). Antennomere 1 approximately 2 times longer than wide, 2–3 subquadrate, 4–6 longer than wide, 7–10 subquadrate. Frontal sulcus deep and reaching hind point of eye from frontal rostral lobes. Anterior frontal fovea an inverted triangle. Posterior frontal fovea elongate. Eye prominent, one-half length of temple. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1110,1192,725,746]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Thorax:</emphasis>
Prosternum as long as wide, widest at midpoint. Elytra approximately triangular (
<figureCitation box="[1027,1113,778,799]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="25.[175,207,1562,1581]" captionTargetBox="[158,1164,200,1538]" captionTargetId="figure-1@25.[151,1171,183,1548]" captionTargetPageId="25" captionText="Fig. 11. Habitus of Sagola species in the bifida species-group, dorsal views. a) S. bifida, b) S. latistriata, c) S. crawi, d) S. earlyi, e) S. embersoni, f) S. mayae, g) S. ranatungae, h) S. baylessae, i) S. tekoauensis, j) S. ferroi, k) S. fairburni. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4907771" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4907771/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 11k</figureCitation>
). Meso-and metathorax trapezoidal, longer than wide. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[707,815,832,853]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Abdomen:</emphasis>
Male tergite IV without microtrichial patch. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[784,903,858,879]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Aedeagus:</emphasis>
Median lobe longer than parameres with semicircular depression (
<figureCitation box="[1098,1182,885,906]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="26.[197,229,1062,1081]" captionTargetBox="[178,1187,186,1039]" captionTargetId="figure-283@26.[173,1193,183,1044]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="Fig. 12. Sagola species in the bifida species-group. Aedeagi, dorsal views: a) S. bifida, b) S. latistriata, c) S. crawi, d) S. earlyi, e) S. embersoni, f) S. mayae, g) S. ranatungae, h) S. baylessae, i) S. tekoauensis, j) S. ferroi, k) S. fairburni. S. latistriata, male: l) Dorsal surface of head, m) Ventral surface of head (arrow indicates large depression), n) Mid-femur, lateral view (arrow indicates shallow depression), o) Mid-tibia, lateral view (arrow indicates bend). Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4907775" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4907775/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 12k</figureCitation>
). Phallobase of median lobe asymmetrical and triangular (
<figureCitation box="[796,884,938,959]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="26.[197,229,1062,1081]" captionTargetBox="[178,1187,186,1039]" captionTargetId="figure-283@26.[173,1193,183,1044]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="Fig. 12. Sagola species in the bifida species-group. Aedeagi, dorsal views: a) S. bifida, b) S. latistriata, c) S. crawi, d) S. earlyi, e) S. embersoni, f) S. mayae, g) S. ranatungae, h) S. baylessae, i) S. tekoauensis, j) S. ferroi, k) S. fairburni. S. latistriata, male: l) Dorsal surface of head, m) Ventral surface of head (arrow indicates large depression), n) Mid-femur, lateral view (arrow indicates shallow depression), o) Mid-tibia, lateral view (arrow indicates bend). Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4907775" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4907775/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 12k</figureCitation>
). Parameres asymmetrical, left paramere blunt and right triangular (
<figureCitation box="[1075,1163,964,985]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="26.[197,229,1062,1081]" captionTargetBox="[178,1187,186,1039]" captionTargetId="figure-283@26.[173,1193,183,1044]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="Fig. 12. Sagola species in the bifida species-group. Aedeagi, dorsal views: a) S. bifida, b) S. latistriata, c) S. crawi, d) S. earlyi, e) S. embersoni, f) S. mayae, g) S. ranatungae, h) S. baylessae, i) S. tekoauensis, j) S. ferroi, k) S. fairburni. S. latistriata, male: l) Dorsal surface of head, m) Ventral surface of head (arrow indicates large depression), n) Mid-femur, lateral view (arrow indicates shallow depression), o) Mid-tibia, lateral view (arrow indicates bend). Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4907775" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4907775/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 12k</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
